  <p><strong><a name="gather">WHAT INFORMATION DO WE GATHER AND TRACK?</a></strong><a href="#top"><small> (back to top) </small></a><br>
    At StartupDiscovery, we take your privacy very seriously. We are not in the business of disclosing your personally
    identifiable information to others without your express or implied consent. We record IP addresses (the Internet
    address of a computer) to track sessions on our Website. Tracking gives us an idea of which parts and pages of our
    site users are visiting, how often they visit them, and how long they spend there. We also track browser type and
    platform. We use this information to deliver customized information specific to a particular platform and to
    determine the “mix” of browser types accessing our Website. This information helps us make our Website operate
    correctly with your browser.</p>

  <p>In addition, some of our products and services may include technology that, if an Internet or Wi-Fi connection is
    available, contacts StartupDiscovery servers with basic information about your mobile phone or mobile data device
    and the operating system and the types of programs it is used with. In some instances and with some of our products,
    the location of your mobile phone may be collected and utilized by StartupDiscovery to provide you with the best
    service possible.</p>

  <p><strong><a name="cookies">COOKIES AND HOW WE USE THEM</a></strong><a href="#top"><small> (back to top) </small></a><br>
    Cookies are unique text files that are sent to your browser from a web server. As you browse our Website, cookies
    are placed on your computer’s hard drive including when you download, register and/or purchase software. Cookies may
    include registration numbers for any or all of your registered StartupDiscovery products. Because some cookies may
    contain registration number(s), they can be linked to personally identifiable information. StartupDiscovery does not
    provide any personally identifiable information from cookie data to third parties. StartupDiscovery may use a third
    party to analyze for StartupDiscovery general Website statistics such as number of pages viewed, browser types, etc.
    obtained from cookies.</p>

  <p>Cookies are used by StartupDiscovery for the following:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>To track the method of your referral to our Website;</li>
    <li>Anonymous statistical purposes;</li>
    <li>To track your site session and present information, graphics or hyperlinks based on your session and/or write
      information to submission forms when contacting StartupDiscovery; and
    </li>
    <li>To present information, offers and invitations (surveys, beta programs, etc.) based on your product registration
      and improve your experience with the site.
    </li>
  </ul>
